Libsklog - Make secure logging using Schneier and Kelsey scheme
===============================================================

	Copyright (C) 2007-2010 Politecnico di Torino, Italy
	TORSEC group -- http://security.polito.it

Libsklog is a C language library which makes possible the generation
of log entries by following the scheme defined by B.Schneier ad J.Kelsey
in "Secure Audit Logs to Support Computer Forensics".

Installation notes
------------------

1) Prerequisites

    OpenSSL >= 0.9.8
    SQLite3.x
    Libconfuse
    Libuuid

2) Get sources

    2.1) Using GIT

        $ git clone <URL> libsklog
    
    2.2) Using SVN

        $ svn co <URL> libsklog 
    
    2.2) Download tarball

        $ wget libsklog-<VERSION>.tar.gz

3) Building

    3.1) If GIT or SVN was used

        $ cd <directory where libsklog was cloned/checkout'ed>
        $ mkdir m4
        $ autoreconf --verbose --force --install
        $ ./configure --prefix=/usr/local --enable-debug --enable-trace
        $ make
        $ make install (as root)

    3.2) If tarball was downloaded

        $ mkdir temp
        $ cd temp
        $ tar zxvf libsklog-<VERSION>.tar.gz
        $ cd libsklog-<VERSION>
        $ ./configure --prefix=/usr/local --enable-debug --enable-trace
        $ make
        $ make install (as root)

